OL,7,FMr McKone said Callaghan took the boy
OL,8,Fon "frequent" outings in his car,
OL,9,Ftaking him shopping in York and for a
OL,10,Fpub lunch, also giving him a silver
OL,11,Fcigarette box on another occasion.
OL,13,FHe said Callaghan would ask the boy to
OL,14,Fmeet him after Mass on Saturday
OL,15,Fevenings at different locations,
OL,16,Fincluding guest rooms.
OL,18,FThe complainant told police there was
OL,19,F"lots of hugs, lots of touching, I was
OL,20,Fmade to feel really special".
