OL,7,FThe court heard Callaghan had admitted
OL,8,Fto having "some sexual activity" with
OL,9,Fthe first complainant, "but only after
OL,10,Fhe was 16 and only with his consent".
OL,12,FMr McKone said: "Whatever (the
OL,13,Fcomplainant's) age, this was not true
OL,14,Fconsent ` this was not consent given
OL,15,Ffreely by someone who had a real
OL,16,Fchoice."
OL,18,FCallaghan is charged with 12 counts of
OL,19,Findecently assaulting the boy, with
OL,20,Ffour alleged to have happened when he
OL,21,Fwas under 16.
